    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>Which of the following is the least?</p>\n\n<p>12% of 625</p>\n\n<p>15% of 555</p>\n\n<p>10% of 720</p>\n\n<p>9% of 845</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "1",
        "content": "9% of 845"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "2",
        "content": "12% of 625"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "3",
        "content": "10% of 720"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "4",
        "content": "15% of 555"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "3"
    ],
    "explanation": "<p>We are asked which of the following is the <strong>least</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>12% of 625  </p></li>\n<li><p>15% of 555  </p></li>\n<li><p>10% of 720  </p></li>\n<li><p>9% of 845  </p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Step 1: Calculate each option</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>12% of 625</strong>  </li>\n</ol>\n<p>$ = \\frac{12}{100} \\times 625 = 0.12 \\times 625 = 75 $</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><strong>15% of 555</strong>  </li>\n</ol>\n<p>$ = \\frac{15}{100} \\times 555 = 0.15 \\times 555 = 83.25 $</p>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li><strong>10% of 720</strong>  </li>\n</ol>\n<p>$ = \\frac{10}{100} \\times 720 = 0.10 \\times 720 = 72 $</p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li><strong>9% of 845</strong>  </li>\n</ol>\n<p>$ = \\frac{9}{100} \\times 845 = 0.09 \\times 845 = 76.05 $</p>\n\n<p><strong>Step 2: Compare values</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>12% of 625 = <strong>75</strong>  </p></li>\n<li><p>15% of 555 = <strong>83.25</strong>  </p></li>\n<li><p>10% of 720 = <strong>72</strong>  </p></li>\n<li><p>9% of 845 = <strong>76.05</strong></p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>✅ The <strong>least</strong> value is <strong>72</strong> = <strong>10% of 720</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Final Answer:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Option 3: 10% of 720</strong></p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ssc-cgl-tier-i-26th-july-2023-shift-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "Ravi initially used to save 20% of his monthly income. Recently his monthly income&nbsp;was raised by 25%. His nominal savings also went up by 5%. What percentage of his&nbsp;present nominal income does Ravi currently save?",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "1",
        "content": "25%"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "2",
        "content": "20%"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "3",
        "content": "15%"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "4",
        "content": "16.8%"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "4"
    ],
    "explanation": "<h3>Step 1: Assume initial income</h3>\n<p>Let Ravi’s initial monthly income = <strong>100 units</strong>.  </p>\n<p>His savings rate = <strong>20%</strong> → savings = <strong>20 units</strong>.  </p>\n<p>So initial expenditure = 100 – 20 = <strong>80 units</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3>Step 2: Income after the raise</h3>\n<p>Income increases by <strong>25%</strong> → New income = 100 × 1.25 = <strong>125 units</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3>Step 3: New savings</h3>\n<p>We’re told <strong>nominal savings went up by 5%</strong>.  </p>\n<p>That means new savings = 20 × 1.05 = <strong>21 units</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3>Step 4: Calculate percentage of current income saved</h3>\n<p>Percentage saved = (new savings / new income) × 100  </p>\n<p>= (21 / 125) × 100  </p>\n<p>= <strong>16.8%</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>✅ Correct Answer: <strong>Option 4 → 16.8%</strong></p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "ssc-cgl-tier-i-26th-july-2023-shift-1",
    "difficulty": null
  }
